        <section id="page-reflections" class="portfolio-page">
            <div class="section-header">
                <span class="subtitle">Retrospective</span>
                <h2>Key Reflections</h2>
            </div>

            <p class="learning-intro-para">
                Building a complete project case study was one of the most challenging and rewarding parts of my engineering journey so far. It taught me how to think beyond code and communicate decisions clearly.
            </p>

            <div class="reflections-masonry">
                
                <div class="neon-card reflection-masonry-card">
                    <div class="reflection-card-number">01</div>
                    <h4 style="font-size:1.2rem; margin-bottom:0.5rem; color:var(--accent-orange);">🤝 Collaborative Coding beats Solo Dev</h4>
                    <p>Working in a team of five (Atharva, Ashutosh, Yashwant, Anoosha, and myself) taught me the value of delegation, alignment, and source control. Building different modules of the CCTV platform required clear interfaces and mutual trust.</p>
                    <div class="reflection-quote-block">
                        <p>"Software engineering is a team sport; code is only as clean as the team's communication."</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="neon-card reflection-masonry-card">
                    <div class="reflection-card-number">02</div>
                    <h4 style="font-size:1.2rem; margin-bottom:0.5rem; color:var(--accent-orange);">🔌 Bridging Frontend & Backend Logic</h4>
                    <p>Connecting React state flows to an Express backend was a massive learning loop. Understanding how database queries, middleware security gates, and REST controllers interact has shifted my perspective to system-level thinking.</p>
                    <div class="reflection-quote-block">
                        <p>"An interface is just a window; the real magic happens in the data pipeline behind it."</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="neon-card reflection-masonry-card">
                    <div class="reflection-card-number">03</div>
                    <h4 style="font-size:1.2rem; margin-bottom:0.5rem; color:var(--accent-orange);">💾 Seeding Workflows & Database Sync</h4>
                    <p>Managing product seeding files containing over 400 lines of CCTV catalog components forced me to learn schema normalization, migration safety, and how to verify backend database connections early on.</p>
                    <div class="reflection-quote-block">
                        <p>"Design schemas for tomorrow's queries, but parse files for today's database seeds."</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="neon-card reflection-masonry-card" style="grid-column: span 2;">
                    <div class="reflection-card-number">04</div>
                    <h4 style="font-size:1.2rem; margin-bottom:0.5rem; color:var(--accent-orange);">⏱️ Agile Sprints & Incremental Slices</h4>
                    <p>Splitting our work into Sprints made the project highly manageable. We learned to ship incremental working features, debug them in parallel, and continuously review progress together during team standups.</p>
                    <div class="reflection-quote-block">
                        <p>"Sprints divide complex backlogs into measurable checkpoints of working software."</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </section>

